name: Against The Stream
description: Against the stream is for the people that don\'t follow the crowd. The individuals that are brave and just a little bit crazy. The dreamers for a better world.

The musical concept is to dedicate each of the 12 episodes during this year to a certain mood or a genre. Some examples that are in the plan: Ambient, Balearic, Trancy/Rave, or something seasonal like one dedicated to the coldest and one to the hottest season.

DJ Ulterior has been active in the Skopje clubbing scene for about 15 years, both as a clubber and as a DJ. His life is dedicated to finding, sorting and presenting music in front of other people. His goal is to share the good feeling that music creates for himself, with other people.

name: Analog Shuffle
description: In house barista AKA selector of good vibes. Broadcasting once per month, on a Saturday, from 12:00.

name: Andreja Salpe
description: Andreja Salpe is the person behind PMG Tanz Digital who is involved in the electronic duos Barum Barum and DJ Magija. His “invites” show is a monthly, 2 hour long residency where he will be joined by friends and guests from all over.

name: Any sound is valid
fullName: Any sound is valid - aka thesaur
description: The self-explanatory title is about actually considering any music/sound as a valid sound. it is about merging and blending multiple styles of music in one set that will create an experimental atmosphere. finding inspiration in every corner of sub-genres is the main motive of showcasing "any sound is valid".

akathesaur is a local artist who mainly focused on music. As a musician, he released one album and his music is often called  "DIY" experimental/trip-hop mixed with spoken words and a hint of classical background. He started his DJ career at Shortbus where he has his first residency, he got to meet other local DJ\'s and get to know the scene. As a newcomer DJ, aims to break the concepts of monochromatic music genres usually faced on the local club scene. Started with Techno/leftfield techno, Acid House, and other current genres, as discovering more music genres, akathesaur found freedom by blending multiple genres in one set and resulting in more experimental expression.

name: Audiobahn
description: Bodan Jamakoski is a Macedonian DJ and producer from Skopje, Macedonia. His career started seven years ago as part of the renowned Macedonian collective BTKRSH. After spending a couple of years DJing and being resident in some of the clubs in Skopje, he started focusing on his own music production. He has released EP’s for Juan’s Kitchen Delights Recordings, PMG Recordings and TMM , his passion for sharing and promoting quality electronic music inspired him to start the project Audiobahn in collaboration with a friend.

Audiobahn is the first live streaming platform in Macedonia, conceived as a place for promoting quality electronic music, performances and art through different kinds of events and ambients. Years later, the concept of Audiobahn has expanded into organizing live streamed events at unusual “hidden” locations around Skopje, with limited invitations, which sparked a huge interest by the electronic music lovers.

name: Bottom Funk
description: Constant search for the thrill of finding hidden grooves, that one amazing jam that is worth collecting the record is what has driven me for decades to dig for records. I still get excited every time the needle touches the record.  It is pure magic!  And if the tune has the groove with lots of soul, jazz, or funk…it is always a home run.  I will try to transcend some of that magic by selecting good music from my vinyl collection for my new joint @AMOKRadio simply called BOTTOM FUNK… where I will always get to the bottom of the funk. Promo show is pre-recorded due to Covid…but hopefully I’ll hit the waves LIVE next month.  Stay tuned…

shows.name: Bottom Funk - James Brown Tribute - George Cvetkovski

name: Bushava Muzika
description: The name of the show Bushava Muzika didn\'t come unknowingly. The goal is to select, listen and talk about different genres: be it electronic, jazz, indie, pop etc. A selection of old and new releases, LP\'s and EP\'s, followed up by discussing them. Selecting favorites from her record collection and in-store picks and fusing them together for a listening mix. Creating eclectic mixes where listeners can hear all kinds of sounds. Plus, expect live jams with an electron, a midi piano and other instruments.

name: Formless
description: Born in the late 80\'s, Bruv has grown up under a strong domestic influence of funk, soul and disco. Later, through his knowledge of music production software, his interest in other branches of electronic music like drum & bass, techno, house and trip-hop has grown further.

In 2012, he became a member of the D2 collective and a resident of the club Kapan An. Later, Bruv becomes a part of the BTKRSH team where his focus gradually shifts more towards house and techno. Between 2014 and 2016 he was part of Radio MOF, presenting new electronic music releases together with Dijana (D.Lite/Diah).

When it comes to his style, he is almost always different. His sets can range from house and disco to techno and electro, and he would simply describe his sets as versatile, dynamic and energetic. Besides his residency and Kapan An, Bruv played in almost all underground clubs in Skopje and since 2018 is a resident of the club Sektor 909.

name: Gap Year
description: Inspired by the unusual sounds that can be found in the electronic music, Nastasyakish looks for interesting ways of combining and sharing them with the crowd. You can expect a lot of different styles, from slow burners to up-tempo acid. Belgrade and St. Petersburg are some of the places she played aside from local clubs (also residency at Minus 1 )and festivals. She is an active member of the cultural collective Skopski Groove, the already well established online record store - Wax Revival & now part of the crew at Amok Radio.

name: Groovin High
description: Chakra is the name and Jazz is the game. Jazz and everything closely related. Revolving around the genre, "Groovin\' High" will be blending modern jazz, bebop, hard bop, postbop and spiritual with souljazz, funk, soul and latin jazz, while stretching from Dizzy Gillespie and Herbie Hancock, to Curtis Mayfield and Mongo Santamaria.

Bojan Chakra is a musical enthusiast and jazz fanatic from Skopje. Being a passionate vinyl collector, through the last decade he’s been selecting music of his own taste, at the local and regional bars for several days a week. For the past year Bojan is hosting several weekly and monthly shows on various online radios and will be hosting his own monthly show on Amok Radio.

name: Hello & Goodbye
description: Everything we do happens between one Hello and one Goodbye. Whether it is a Dj set, or a walk in the park, there always is a Hello somewhere in the beginning and a Goodbye in the end.
So we have here, on Wednesday, the 3rd of February, our first Hello at Amok Radio, from many to come.  Stay tuned for a lot of vibes and divergent content. Goodbye...

name: Lasya
description: The term Lāsya , in the context of Hindu mythology, describes the dance performed by Goddess Parvati as it expresses love, care, happiness and is filled with grace and beauty.  The Lasya was the second phase of creation, in response to Shiva\'s Tandava dance that gave birth to the Universe.  It combined to form the triad, "laya" and "pralaya" “ shunya” the cyclic motion of things from resonance to dissolution, from stillness to movement, from those two sounds to silence. In a literal sense, Lāsya means "softer" beauty, happiness, enchanting, and grace.

name: Monthly Operation
fullName: Monthly Operation - Soul Case, Eternal Love & Barbara Boeing
description: A monthly, 2 hour long show on Saturdays covering a wide selection of styles, tempos and decades. Tropical beaches and dark alleys. From my heart to your ears. That’s what I do. Expect some guests in the second half of the show.

Soul Case is the alias of Bojan Janev, a Skopje based DJ, digger and promoter. As a founder of “Oubli” and the more recent “Amok Radio”, he is constantly trying to push things forward – personally, but also in terms of diversifying and strengthening things locally.

At only 25 years of age, he has become a staple in Skopje’s underground scene, holding various residencies at the legendary “Sektor 909” and the more recent “Minus Eden” club. He hasn’t gone unnoticed outside the country’s borders too – having spun records across dancefloors in Belgrade, Berlin, Tokyo, Osaka and South Korea.

Coming as a part from the music collective "Oubli", now joining forces with Skopski Groove and Wax Revival Store as Amok Radio he established himself as a solid pusher on the dance scene in Skopje, even holding a two year residency at "Sektor 909".

name: Soundcentric
description: Think about sound. Intrinsically sound has always been the focal point, the center or simply “Soundcentric”. Challenge yourself to nurture different sounds into melody and rhythm, tangled with harmony. Podcast every third Thursday of the month for every sound explorer, just like us.
Who we are? Milan, Bojan and Filip.

name: Space Diversity
tags: Downtempo, Street Soul, Acid Jazz, Soul, Funk, House, Hip-Hop
description: Space Diversity is electromagnetic waves transmission technique which uses two or more receiving and transmitting antennas to improve signal integrity. Space Diversity is mounthly Show hosted by Belgrade based Danilo Kas, which transmits musical diversity to all of your recievers. From the past to the future, from the soul to the dancefloors, cafefully selected with passion and love!

name: Street Struck
description: Being struck by all the quality music coming out the streets, through different eras, places, spaces and genres, Double G and friends team up to deliver the street sound on-air twice a month.

Double G, Skopje based DJ and collector, bought his first pair of turntables and a mixer in late 2016, starting to spin hip hop at private parties which later served as one of the inspirations to form the cultural collective Skopski Groove, alongside other creative individuals. He is also one of the founders of the record store Wax Revival, and a part of the crew behind Amok Radio. His sets are eclectic, ranging across all types of genres and styles. With a deep passion for the 7” vinyl format, you can often hear him spinning 7” only sets.
